        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 26. Aeduella blainvillei (AGASSIZ, 1833). a, b – drawing and photograph (whitened) of the skull roof in dorsal view. MHK 82787. Scale bars 5 mm. c, d, e, f, g – isolated bones of the rostral part and the skull roof. The arrow indicates the front for all bones. Scale bar represents 5 mm for all bones. c – rostro-postrostral. MHK 82788. d – right supraorbital anterior in lateral view. MHK 82782. e – left parietal in dorsal view with two pit lines. MHK 82804. f – right parietal in dorsal view with two pit lines. MHK 82785. g – right frontal in dorsal view with pores of the supraorbital sensory canal. MHK 82767. Abbreviations: Dsph – dermosphenotic; Fr – frontal; ioc – infraorbital canal; Pa – parietal; pl – pit line; Rpr – rostropostrostral; soc – supraorbital canal; Sorb – supraorbital." ;
