<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4586567>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 29. Aeduella blainvillei (AGASSIZ, 1833). a – anterior part of left maxilla of juvenile specimen in lateral view. The maxilla is 9 mm long. Arrows delimit the fragments of tubular teeth figured at b of this Text-fig. Specimen G 4/2. Scale bar 1 mm. b – fragments of short strong tubules of tubular teeth. The teeth-cusps are broken. G 4/2. Scale bar 100 μm. c – anterior part of left maxilla of juvenile specimen. The maxilla is 12 mm long. Frame marks the view at d of this Text-fig. G 4/1. Scale bar 1 mm. d – isolated short tubular tooth of juvenile specimen. Tubule of the tooth is short and strong. It is terminated apically by the tooth-cusp. G 4/1. Scale bar 100 μm. e – anterior part of left maxilla of adult specimen in lateral view. The maxilla is 21 mm long. Tubular teeth with long tubules are covered from lateral side by maxillary bone and only short teeth-cusps project on the ventral edge of the maxillary. The arrows indicate the positioning of the tubular tooth on the maxillary. G 6. Scale bar 1 mm. f – middle part of the ventral edge of the same maxilla as at a of this Text-fig. with isolated tubular tooth (marked by the frame) which is figured at higher magnification at g of this Text-fig. G 6. Scale bar 1 mm. g – isolated tubular tooth of adult specimen partially overlapped by the sediment. The tooth consists of very long slender tubules which are terminated by small sharply pointed tooth-cusp. G 6. Scale bar 100 μm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4586567/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4586557>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Text-fig. 23. Progyrolepis heyleri POPLIN, 1999. a – a scale from the middle part of the lateral side of the body with conspicuous ridges arranged diagonally across the scale. MHK 82831, whitened. Scale bar 1 mm. b – small tubercles which form the microsculpture on the scale have elliptical base, antero-posteriorly elongated, and are arranged diagonally in the same direction as the ridges on Text-fig. 23a. MHK 82831. Scale bars 100 μm. c, d – photograph and drawing of a scale with a pore of the lateral sensory line. D 08.02.98.10.4/4, whitened. Scale bar 1 mm. e – drawing of a scale from the middle part of the lateral side of the body. D 04.11.95.10. Scale bar 1 mm. f – drawing of a scale from the anterior region of the body above the lateral sensory line. D 05.09.98. Scale bar 1 mm. g – drawing of a scale from the lateral side of the body between the lateral sensory line and the base of the pelvic fin. D 18.13.96.7. Scale bar 1 mm. h – drawing of a scale from the abdominal region of the body in front of the pelvic fin. BX 31.05.99.49. Scale bar 1 mm. i – large basal fulcra from the dorsal rim of the caudal peduncle. BX 28.01.99.8. Scale bar 5 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4586557/files/figure.png" .

